ollins.  \n |LineColor=fa9d6e\n}}{{#invoke:Episode list|sublist|Law & Order (season 2)\n |EpisodeNumber=33\n |EpisodeNumber2=11\n |Title=His Hour Upon the Stage\n |DirectedBy=Steve Cohen\n |WrittenBy=Robert Nathan & [[Giles Blunt]]\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1991|12|10}}\n |ProdCode=67407\n |Aux4=18.30{{fact|date=March 2020}}\n |ShortSummary=The discovery of a frozen corpse in a dumpster leads to rival Broadway producers.\n |LineColor=fa9d6e\n}}{{#invoke:Episode list|sublist|Law & Order (season 2)\n |EpisodeNumber=34\n |EpisodeNumber2=12\n |Title=Star Struck\n |DirectedBy=Ed Sherin\n |WrittenBy={{StoryTeleplay\n | s = David Black & Alan Gelb;\n | t = Robert Nathan & Sally Nemeth\n | slabel = {{abbr|S|Story by}}\n | tlabel = {{abbr|T|Teleplay by}}\n }}\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1992|1|7}}\n |ProdCode=67406\n |Aux4=21.30{{fact|date=March 2020}}\n |ShortSummary=An obsessive fan pleads temporary insanity when he is charged with attempting to murder the soap opera actress who is the center of his life.\n* Based on the murder of the actress [[Rebecca Schaeffer]].\n |LineColor=fa9d6e\n}}{{#invoke:Episode list|sublist|Law & Order (season 2)\n |EpisodeNumber=35\n |EpisodeNumber2=13\n |Title=Severance\n |DirectedBy=[[James Frawley|Jim Frawley]]\n |WrittenBy={{StoryTeleplay\n | s = Michael Duggan;\n | t = Michael S. Chernuchin;\n | ex1 = William N. Fordes\n | slabel = {{abbr|S|Story by}}\n | tlabel = {{abbr|T|Teleplay by}}\n | ex1label = {{abbr|S/T|Story and teleplay by}}\n }}\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1992|1|14}}\n |ProdCode=67418\n |Aux4=17.40{{fact|date=March 2020}}\n |ShortSummary=Stone faces an old rival in court as he tries to link a hit man and three murders to a sleazy lawyer and a powerful man behind bars.\n |LineColor=fa9d6e\n}}{{#invoke:Episode list|sublist|Law & Order (season 2)\n |EpisodeNumber=36\n |EpisodeNumber2=14\n |Title=Blood Is Thicker\n |DirectedBy=[[Peter Levin]]\n |WrittenBy={{StoryTeleplay\n | s = Robert Nathan;\n | ex1 = Ed Zuckerman\