lice battle the closed ranks of the Navy to investigate the death of a female Naval officer during a party in a Manhattan hotel.\n* Based on the 1991 [[Tailhook scandal]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tv.yahoo.com/photos/stars-on-law-order-before-their-big-break-slideshow/julianna-margulies-93-conduct-unbecoming-photo-1346283357.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2013-07-15 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120906054600/http://tv.yahoo.com/photos/stars-on-law-order-before-their-big-break-slideshow/julianna-margulies-93-conduct-unbecoming-photo-1346283357.html |archivedate=2012-09-06 }}</ref>\n |LineColor=000000\n}}{{#invoke:Episode list|sublist|Law & Order (season 3)\n |EpisodeNumber=62\n |EpisodeNumber2=18\n |Title=Animal Instinct\n |DirectedBy=Ed Sherin\n |WrittenBy=Michael S. Chernuchin & Sibyl Gardner\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1993|3|17}}\n |ProdCode=68021\n |Aux4=12.70<ref>{{cite news |last1=Gable |first1=Donna |title=Waco standoff lifts CBS' '48 Hours' |date = 24 March 1993 |work=USA TODAY}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary=The initial investigation into the death of a research scientist leads to an animal-rights group until evidence surfaces that her husband's affair with a coworker may point to a possible motive for the murder.  When the husband is acquitted, the investigation turns to the individual who provided evidence of the affair. \n |LineColor=000000\n}}{{#invoke:Episode list|sublist|Law & Order (season 3)\n |EpisodeNumber=63\n |EpisodeNumber2=19\n |Title=Virus\n |DirectedBy=[[Steven Robman]]\n |WrittenBy=Michael S. Chernuchin & Ren\u00e9 Balcer\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1993|4|21}}\n |ProdCode=68010\n |Aux4=11.90<ref>{{cite news |last1=Donion |first1=Brian |last2=Daniels |first2=Charlene |title='Walker' kicks in for CBS |work=USA TODAY |date=28 April 1993}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary=While investigating several deaths at a diabetes clinic, Briscoe and Logan discover that teenage computer hackers may have tampered with the clinic'