ernally.\n* This episode was later remade as ''[[Law & Order: UK]]'' season 2 episode titled \"Love and Loss\".\n |LineColor=000000\n}}{{#invoke:Episode list|sublist|Law & Order (season 3)\n |EpisodeNumber=55\n |EpisodeNumber2=11\n |Title=Extended Family\n |DirectedBy=[[Charles Correll (director)|Charles Correll]]\n |WrittenBy={{StoryTeleplay\n | t = Robert Nathan;\n | ex1 = Wendell Rawls\n | tlabel = {{abbr|T|Teleplay by}}\n | ex1label = {{abbr|S/T|Story and teleplay by}}\n }}\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1993|1|6}}\n |ProdCode=68015\n |Aux4=16.10<ref>{{cite news |last1=Daniels |first1=Charlene |title=Women help push CBS to victory |work=USA TODAY |date=13 January 1993}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary=When Janet Silver kidnaps her daughter from the mall, Logan and Briscoe are sent in to investigate and learn that she committed the crime with the assistance of a children's help organization after going to them with fears that the little girl's father was sexually abusing her.\n |LineColor=000000\n}}{{#invoke:Episode list|sublist|Law & Order (season 3)\n |EpisodeNumber=56\n |EpisodeNumber2=12\n |Title=Right to Counsel\n |DirectedBy=James Frawley\n |WrittenBy=Michael S. Chernuchin & Barry M. Schkolnick\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1993|1|13}}\n |ProdCode=68019\n |Aux4=15.10<ref>{{cite news |last1=Donion |first1=Brian |title=ABC gets a Thursday night boost |work=USA TODAY |date=30 January 1993 |pages=3D}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary=After Stone accepts a plea bargain from the much younger and poorer lover of a wealthy older woman found murdered in her apartment, he begins to have doubts that he has sent the right man to prison, especially as he learns more about the attorney who handled the woman's estate.\n |LineColor=000000\n}}{{#invoke:Episode list|sublist|Law & Order (season 3)\n |EpisodeNumber=57\n |EpisodeNumber2=13\n |Title=Night and Fog\n |DirectedBy=Ed Sherin\n |WrittenBy=Michael S. Chernuchin & Ren\u00e9 Balcer\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1993|2|3}}\n |ProdCode=68