rev_season          = [[Law & Order (season 4)|Season 4]]\n| next_season          = [[Law & Order (season 6)|Season 6]]\n| episode_list         = List of Law & Order episodes\n}}\nThe fifth season of ''[[Law & Order]]'' aired on [[NBC]] between September 21, 1994, and May 24, 1995.\n\n==Cast==\n[[Jack McCoy]] (played by [[Sam Waterston]]) replaced season 4's [[Benjamin Stone (character)|Ben Stone]] ([[Michael Moriarty]]) as Executive Assistant District Attorney. [[Mike Logan (Law & Order)|Mike Logan]] (played by [[Chris Noth]]) departed the cast after this season, thus making [[Adam Schiff (Law & Order)|Adam Schiff]] (played by [[Steven Hill]]) the last remaining first-season cast member.\n\n===Main cast===\n* [[Jerry Orbach]] as [[Lennie Briscoe|Det. Lennie Briscoe]]\n* [[Chris Noth]] as [[Mike Logan (Law & Order)|Det. Mike Logan]]\n* [[S. Epatha Merkerson]] as [[Anita Van Buren]]\n* [[Sam Waterston]] as EADA [[Jack McCoy]]\n* [[Jill Hennessy]] as [[Claire Kincaid|A.D.A. Claire Kincaid]]\n* [[Steven Hill]] as [[Adam Schiff (Law & Order)|D.A. Adam Schiff]]\n\n===Recurring cast===\n* [[Dann Florek]] as [[Donald Cragen|Capt. Don Cragen]]\n* [[Carolyn McCormick]] as [[Elizabeth Olivet]]\n\n==Episodes==\n<onlyinclude>\n{{#invoke:Episode table|main\n|background  = #A12240\n|overall     = \n|season      = \n|title       = \n|director    =\n|writer      = \n|airdate     = \n|prodcode    = \n|viewers     = \n|country     = US\n|episodes    = \n{{#invoke:Episode list|sublist|Law & Order (season 5)\n |EpisodeNumber=89\n |EpisodeNumber2=1\n |Title=Second Opinion\n |DirectedBy=[[Edwin Sherin|Ed Sherin]]\n |WrittenBy=[[Michael S. Chernuchin]] & Jeremy R. Littman\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1994|9|21}}\n |ProdCode=69408\n |Aux4=18.30<ref>{{cite news |title=NIELSEN RATINGS |work=USA TODAY |date=28 September 1994 |page=3D}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary=A woman's death exposes an unorthodox method of treating cancer that new Executive Assistant DA McCoy intends to prove is negligent ho