{"title_page": "Goldstein (surname)", "text_new": "'''Goldstein''' ({{IPAc-en|'|g|o\u028a|l|d|s|t|i\u02d0|n|,_|-|s|t|a\u026a|n}}; {{IPA-de|\u02c8\u0261o\u02d0lt\u0283ta\u026an|lang}}) is a Jewish surname, it translates to \"gold stone\" in English. Notable people with the surname include:\n{{TOC right}}\n== Arts ==\n* [[Adam Goldstein]] (1973\u20132009), American musician and disc jockey known as DJ AM\n* [[Boris Goldstein]] (1922\u20131987), [[Soviet people|Soviet]] violin prodigy \n* [[Doug Goldstein]], American tv screenwriter, producer and director\n* [[Elliot Goldstein]] (born 1938), American actor known as [[Elliott Gould]]\n* [[Fanny Goldstein (librarian)]]\n* Harvey Goldstein (born 1944), American bass guitarist known as [[Harvey Brooks (bassist)|Harvey Brooks]]\n* [[Jack Goldstein]], (1945\u20132003), Canadian-American performance and conceptual artist\n* Jack Goldstein (born 1986), vocalist for the British band [[Fixers (band)|Fixers]]\n* [[Jean-Isidore Goldstein]] (1925&mdash;2007), Romanian-French poet known as [[Isidore Isou]]\n* [[Jenette Goldstein]] (born 1960), American actress\n* [[Jerry Goldstein (producer)]]\n* [[Johnny Goldstein]] (born 1991), Israeli musician \n* [[Jonathan Goldstein (composer)|Jonathan Goldstein]] (1968/1969\u20132019), British composer\n* [[Jonathan Goldstein (actor)]]\n* [[Jonathan Goldstein (author)]]\n* [[Jonathan Goldstein (filmmaker)]]\n* [[Lisa Goldstein]] (born 1953), American fantasy and science fiction writer\n* [[Lisa Goldstein (actress)]]\n* [[Martha Goldstein]] (1919\u20132014), American harpsichordist and pianist\n* [[Marvin Goldstein]] (born 1950), American pianist\n* [[Mikhail Goldstein]] (1917&mdash;1989), composer and violinist\n* [[Philip Goldstein]] (1913&mdash;1980), American painter known as [[Philip Guston]]\n* [[R\u00f3za Goldstein]] (1832&mdash;1892), Hungarian mezzo-soprano known as [[R\u00f3za Csillag]]\n* [[Shaike Goldstein-Ophir]] (1928&mdash;1987), Israeli actor, comedian and screenwriter known as [[Shaike Ophir]]\n* [[Sokher Goldstein]] (1859&mdash;1887), Romanian singer and actor\n* [[Sophie Goldstein]] (1861&mdash;1904), Romanian actress known as [[Sophia Karp]]\n\n== Religion ==\n* [[Clifford Goldstein]] (born 1955), [[Seventh-day Adventist Church|Seventh-day Adventist]] author and editor\n* [[Herbert S. Goldstein]] (1890&mdash;1970), American Orthodox rabbi\n* [[Jonathan A. Goldstein]] (1929&mdash;2004), American biblical scholar\n* [[Josef Goldstein]] (1836\u20131899), Austro-Hungarian cantor\n* [[Joseph Goldstein (writer)]]\n* [[Lisa Goldstein (rabbi)]] \n* [[Nachman Goldstein]] (1825&mdash;1894), Tcheriner Rav\n* [[Samuel Goldstein (rabbi)]] \n* [[Warren Goldstein]] (born 1971), Chief Rabbi of [[South Africa]]\n\n== Sport ==\n* [[Abe Goldstein]] (1898&mdash;1977), American bantamweight boxer\n* [[Danielle Goldstein]] (born 1985), American-Israeli show jumper\n* [[Don Goldstein]] (born 1937), American basketball player\n* [[J\u00f8rn Goldstein]] (born 1953), Norwegian [[Olympic games|Olympic]] ice hockey goalie\n* [[Leo Goldstein]], American-Israeli soccer referee\n* [[Lonnie Goldstein]] (1918\u20132013), American baseball player\n* [[Margie Goldstein-Engle]] (born 1958), American equestrian\n* [[Omer Goldstein]] (born 1996), Israeli cyclist\n* [[Paul Goldstein (tennis)]]\n* [[Ralph Goldstein]] (1913\u20131997), American Olympic \u00e9p\u00e9e fencer\n* [[Roy Goldstein]] (born 1993), Israeli cyclist \n* [[Ruby Goldstein]] (1907&mdash;1984), American welterweight boxer\n* [[Samuel Goldstein]] (1945&mdash;1977), American [[Paralympic Games|Paralympian]]\n* [[Shulamit Goldstein]] (born 1968), Israeli [[Olympic games|Olympic]] rhythmic gymnast\n* [[Steven Goldstein (racing driver)]]\n* [[Todd Goldstein]] (born 1988), Australian rules footballer\n\n== Other ==\n* [[Abraham Samuel Goldstein]] (1925\u20132005), Dean of [[Yale Law School]]\n* [[Adam Goldstein (author)]]\n* [[Al Goldstein]] (1936\u20132013), American publisher\n* [[Andy Goldstein]] (born 1973),